<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  preview_publication.ptx
  Candidate preview-ONLY publication file for the PROTEUS question previewer.

  Purpose: render ONE question as a single, self-contained, expanded HTML page
  suitable for embedding. This is OUR file, independent of the cloned book's
  publication file. (The preview build currently passes NO publication file at
  all; core/pretext.py's manifest has no publication attribute, so this ADDS one
  we control; it does not replace the book's.)

  ===========================================================================
  Targets the two quirks seen in the Stage-E render, plus the embed problem:

  1. Multi-page split + index.html redirect stub
     => set <platform portable="yes"/>
     PreTeXt Guide 29.10 / 44.5.12: a single file (equivalent to chunking
     level 0), NO index.html stub, and CSS/JS loaded from a CDN instead of a
     local _static/ bundle (SVG/search inlined). The CDN part is the win: the
     page becomes self-contained, so it embeds as a raw srcdoc string with no
     asset serving at all.

  2. Question born collapsed (must click the title to expand)
     => set <knowl exercise-inline="no"/>
     Inline exercises default to exercise-inline="yes" (born in a click-to-open
     knowl); "no" presents them normally/expanded. (HYPOTHESIS for a bare
     <cardsort> dropped into a section; confirm via the build. If it does not
     un-collapse, the fix is likely wrapping the snippet in an <exercise> inside
     assemble_standalone.)

  ===========================================================================
  Optional levers (toggle and rebuild to compare):

    <css theme="boulder"/>          Masthead-free, PDF-like theme, good for an
                                    embedded preview (Guide 29.10). Delete to
                                    keep the default theme.
    <tableofcontents level="0"/>    No table of contents (44.1.2). A one-question
                                    page has nothing to navigate.

  ===========================================================================
  CAVEAT (Guide 29.10): some interactive elements load via an iframe HTML file
  that portable mode CANNOT inline. A live cardsort widget may therefore fail to
  initialize in a pure single-file embed; the static question (premises/zones
  plus typeset math) should still render, which is what a coder needs. If we
  require the live widget, drop @portable and instead serve the build dir
  (chunking level 0 with a served _static/ bundle).

  TODO when wiring SA: suppress solutions/answers declaratively via
  exercise-component-visibility (Guide 26.4 / 44.1.3) so an authored <solution>
  cannot leak into the preview. Left out here to keep this file verified-only;
  for a <cardsort> it is moot.
-->
<publication>
	<source>
		<directories external="../../assets" generated="../../generated-assets" />
		<version include="proteus" />
	</source>
  <common>
		<chunking level="0" />
		<tableofcontents level="0" />
		<fillin textstyle="underline" mathstyle="shade" />
  </common>
  <html>
    <platform portable="yes"/>
    <knowl 
			example="no"
			example-solution="no"
			project="no"
			task="no"
			figure="no"
			table="no"
			listing="no"
			list="no"
			activity="no"
			exercise-inline="no"
			exercise-divisional="no"
			exercise-worksheet="no"
			exercise-readingquestion="no"
    />
    <css theme="boulder"/>
		<search variant="none" />
		<toc focused="no" />
		<navigation logic="linear" upbutton="no" />
		<cross-references knowled="never" />
		<calculator model="none" activecode="none" />
  </html>
</publication>
